  Incorporation, Art. 16, Rules of Prof.Conduct, Rule 5.5(a), LSA-R.S. foll. 37:221</p>

  <blockquote>
    <p class="footnotetext">Rule 5.5. Unauthorized Practice of Law</p>

    <p class="footnotetext">A lawyer shall not:</p>

    <p class="footnotetext">(a) Practice law in a jurisdiction where doing so violates the regulation of the legal
    profession in that jurisdiction.</p>
  </blockquote>

  <p class="footnotetext"><a href="#_ednref2" name="_edn2" class="fn" id="_edn2">[ii]</a> State Bar Articles of
  Incorporation, Art. 16, Rules of Prof. Conduct, Rule 8.4, LSA-R.S. foll. 37:221</p>

  <blockquote>
    <p class="footnotetext">Rule 8.4. Misconduct.</p>

    <p class="footnotetext">It is professional misconduct for a lawyer to:</p>

    <p class="footnotetext">(a) Violate or attempt to violate the Rules of Professional Conduct, knowingly assist or
    induce another to do so, or to do so through the acts of another;</p>

    <p class="footnotetext">* * * *</p>
  </blockquote>

  <p class="footnotetext"><a href="#_ednref3" name="_edn3" class="fn" id="_edn3">[iii]</a> According to the ABA
  Standards, Knowledge is "the conscious awareness of the nature or attendant circumstances of the conduct but without
  the conscious objective or purpose to accomplish a particular result." Intent is "the conscious objective or purpose
  to accomplish a particular result."</p>

  <p class="footnotetext"><a href="#_ednref4" name="_edn4" class="fn" id="_edn4">[iv]</a> <i>See</i>
  <span class="cite"><i>In re Jones</i>, 98-0207 (La. 3/27/98), <a 
  href="../SC/1998-03-27_1998-0207.htm">708 So.2d 413</a></span>; <span class="cite"><u>In re Brough</u>, 98-0366 (La.
  4/3/98), <a href="../SC/1998-04-03_1998-0366.htm">709 So. 2d 210</a></span>; <span class="cite"><u>In re Richard</u>,
